  "text": "In a coarse-grained PGA, there are many possible schemes for the PPEs to communicate and exchange information about solutions [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] , [CITATION_3] . The objective of communication is to transfer fitter chromosomes from their local populations to other PPEs for parallel exploitation. There are two major models of communication: the isolated island model and the connected island model.",
